<plot>Paul is a working class American who sees his world as Black &amp; White. However as soon as a co-worker of his, which fits the description of a terrorist, shows up, Paul's world suddenly begins to change into something where 'color' is now of importance. With a bad dream almost coming true, Paul fights for his right to prove that his state of mind, and race, is better than anyone else's. It is through a 'show down' in the bathroom which will lead both Paul and the terrorist to open their eyes that Equality is the answer to their problems.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?179996</url></doc>
